I was a Wolfhound -- A/2/27th Inf. in 1967.  I was in more tunnels than I care to count.  Someone asked  why?  It's simple.  Someone &quot;had&quot; to go down and those of us who had the &quot;ability&quot; volunteered.  Soldiers all try  their best to &quot;stand&quot; by each other and do what they are able to.  That feeing or attitude goes with the territory.<br><br>
I once &quot;ran&quot; into a chicken in a tunnel.  I thought that Charlie sent the chicken down the narrow pathway to slow me down.  It worked.<br><br>
The Tunnels of Cu Chi is highly recommended.<br><br>
